<subSubSection id="C3066554FFA1AF38B0CCEB8D76C859F7" pageId="18" pageNumber="549" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA336DFFFA1AF38B0CCEB8D76C859F7" blockId="18.[151,1437,1142,1529]" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">
<emphasis id="B968EACDFFA1AF38B0CCEB8D762659BF" bold="true" box="[199,315,1431,1457]" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Remarks.</emphasis>
Currently, the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D5CFFA1AF38B239EB8D75AF59BF" authorityName="Rondani" authorityYear="1856" box="[562,690,1431,1457]" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Spaziphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B968EACDFFA1AF38B239EB8D75AF59BF" box="[562,690,1431,1457]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Spaziphora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises three species in the world (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8D4B2EFFA1AF38B460EB8D721459BF" author="Ozerov, A. L." box="[1131,1289,1431,1457]" pageId="18" pageNumber="549" pagination="423 - 430" refId="ref12808" refString="Ozerov, A. L. (2011) A review of the world species of the genus Spaziphora Rondani, 1856 (Diptera: Scathophagidae). Russian Entomological Journal, 20, 423 - 430. https: // doi. org / 10.15298 / rusentj. 20.4.08" type="journal article" year="2011">Ozerov, 2011</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C1C4D5CFFA1AF38B516EB8D760F59DB" authorityName="Ozerov. The" authorityYear="2011" class="Insecta" family="Scathophagidae" genus="Spaziphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="549" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomkovichi">
<emphasis id="B968EACDFFA1AF38B516EB8D760F59DB" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="549">Spaziphora tomkovichi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily distinguished from other known congeneric species by having two distinct ventral spure-like tubercles on male sternite V.
</paragraph>
